# Tailwind CSS Standards

## Conditional Classes

Use `clsx` for simple conditionals, `tailwind-merge` (via `twMerge` or a `cn` helper) when merging consumer classes with component defaults.

```tsx
import { twMerge } from 'tailwind-merge';
import clsx from 'clsx';

// Simple conditional
<div className={clsx('rounded-lg', isActive && 'ring-2 ring-blue-500')} />

// Merging with consumer override (design system components)
export function Button({ className, ...props }: ButtonProps) {
  return <button className={twMerge('px-4 py-2 rounded-md font-medium', className)} {...props} />;
}
```

## Design Tokens Over Arbitrary Values

Prefer Tailwind theme values. Avoid arbitrary values (`text-[13px]`, `bg-[#1a2b3c]`).

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<p className="text-[13px] text-[#6b7280]">...</p>

// ✅ GOOD
<p className="text-sm text-gray-500">...</p>
```

If a value doesn't exist in the theme, extend the Tailwind config rather than using arbitrary syntax.

## Responsive Design

Mobile-first: base styles for mobile, then layer up with `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`.

```tsx
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3" />
```

## Dark Mode

Use the `dark:` variant. Every color must have a dark counterpart.

```tsx
<div className="bg-white text-gray-900 dark:bg-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100" />
```

## No `@apply` for Reuse

Extract repeated class sets into React components, not `@apply` in CSS files.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — in CSS
// .card { @apply rounded-lg border p-4 shadow-sm; }

// ✅ GOOD — as a component
export function Card({ className, children }: CardProps) {
  return <div className={twMerge('rounded-lg border p-4 shadow-sm', className)}>{children}</div>;
}
```

## Class Ordering Convention

Order Tailwind classes by concern for readability:

1. **Layout** — `flex`, `grid`, `block`, `relative`
2. **Sizing** — `w-*`, `h-*`, `min-w-*`
3. **Spacing** — `p-*`, `m-*`, `gap-*`
4. **Typography** — `text-*`, `font-*`, `leading-*`
5. **Colors** — `bg-*`, `text-*`, `border-*`
6. **Effects** — `shadow-*`, `opacity-*`, `ring-*`
7. **Transitions** — `transition-*`, `duration-*`

Use the `prettier-plugin-tailwindcss` plugin to automate class sorting.
